      • getClass2InterfaceMap

        @NotNull
public SortedMap<Class<?>,List<Class<?>>> getClass2InterfaceMap()

        Returns:
        a SortedMap relating each class in the getClassHierarchy() to the Interfaces it implements. All values within this Map are non-null, implying that an empty List will be returned for classes not implementing any interfaces.

      • getAllAnnotations

        @NotNull
public SortedSet<Annotation> getAllAnnotations()
        Retrieves a SortedSet containing the Annotations implemented by the source class (or any of its supertypes), for each Annotation which is preserved at runtime (and therefore present within the compiled bytecode file of the getSource() class. Hence, this method can only retrieve Annotations which have RetentionPolicy.RUNTIME
        Returns:
        a SortedSet containing the Annotations implemented by the source class (or any of its supertypes), for Annotations having RetentionPolicy.RUNTIME.

      • getMethods

        @NotNull
public SortedSet<Method> getMethods(boolean declaredMethods)
        Retrieves all Methods found within the getSource() class.
